An abandoned newborn baby was found with umbilical cord stilled attached to it in Chakide Road, KwaMashu, on Tuesday morning, Netcare 911 said. Netcare 911 said when paramedics arrived, they found a newborn baby boy with the umbilical cord still attached. Medics and police rushed the newborn to the clinic. The emergency care practitioner and the nursing staff cut the cord and placed the baby on oxygen to stabilise him until he was well oxygenated and responsive. The child was in the care of nursing staff. Police are investigating.